"It's ours, it's our future," he added, after he was silent, to look at a huge map behind his back.
North, 70 % of Quebec's territory, includes a part of Labrador, which Quebec has always demanded, was specified by the Prime Minister during the press conference.
"This is a traditional attitude that has been repeated by all existing governments.
